BusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: GIRL SCOUT COUNCIL OF COLONIAL COAST

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: GIRL SCOUT COUNCIL OF COLONIAL COAST, A UNITED WAY AGENCY, SERVES GIRLS IN GRADES K-12, IN SOUTHEASTERN VIRGINIA AND NORTHEASTERN NORTH CAROLINA. OUR MISSION IS TO BUILD GIRLS OF COURAGE, CONFIDENCE AND CHARACTER, WHO MAKE THE WORLD A BETTER PLACE.
IRS990.MissionDesc: GIRL SCOUT COUNCIL OF COLONIAL COAST, A UNITED WAY AGENCY, SERVES GIRLS IN GRADES K-12, IN SOUTHEASTERN VIRGINIA AND NORTHEASTERN NORTH CAROLINA. OUR MISSION IS TO BUILD GIRLS OF COURAGE, CONFIDENCE AND CHARACTER, WHO MAKE THE WORLD A BETTER PLACE.
IRS990.Desc: GIRL SCOUTING STARTED IN HAMPTON ROADS IN 1917--HONORING GIRL SCOUTS OF THE USA FOUNDER JULIETTE GORDON LOW'S LEGACY OF DEVELOPING THE FULL POTENTIAL OF GIRLS. GIRL SCOUTS OF THE COLONIAL COAST, CHARTERED IN 1981, SERVES NEARLY 12,000 GIRLS IN GRADES K THROUGH 12, REGARDLESS OF MEANS, IN PARTNERSHIP WITH 5,000 ADULT MENTORS. 56 FULL-TIME AND 25 PART-TIME GIRL SCOUTS OF THE COLONIAL COAST STAFF MEMBERS UTILIZE A MEDLEY OF STRATEGIC PROCESSES TO SERVE GIRLS THROUGHOUT SOUTHEASTERN VIRGINIA AND NORTHEASTERN NORTH CAROLINA. THE COUNCIL IS CHARTERED BY GIRL SCOUTS OF THE USA, THE WORLD'S LARGEST ORGANIZATION DEDICATED TO GIRLS. GIRL SCOUTING BUILDS GIRLS OF COURAGE, CONFIDENCE, AND CHARACTER WHO MAKE THE WORLD A BETTER PLACE. NATIONALLY, THERE ARE 2.6 MILLION GIRL SCOUTS--1.8 MILLION GIRL MEMBERS AND 800,000 ADULT MEMBERS WORKING PRIMARILY AS VOLUNTEERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE COUNCIL HAS A CUSTODIAL RELATIONSHIP WITH OTHER ENTITIES AND REPORTS THOSE ASSETS AS A CUSTODIAL LIABILITY. THE AMOUNT CONSISTS PRIMARILY OF DUES DUE TO NATIONAL AND OTHER SMALL AMOUNTS.
FUNDS ARE USED TO SUPPORT GIRL MEMBERSHIP DUES AND PROGRAM FEES.

THE COUNCIL IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE, EXCEPT ON NET INCOME DERIVED FROM UNRELATED BUSINESS ACTIVITIES. INTERNAL REVENUE CODE SECTION 513(A) DEFINES AN UNRELATED TRADE OR BUSINESS OF AN EXEMPT ORGANIZATION AS ANY TRADE OR BUSINESS WHICH IS NOT SUBSTANTIALLY RELATED TO THE EXERCISE OR PERFORMANCE OF ITS EXEMPT PURPOSE. CURRENTLY, THE COUNCIL HAS NO OBLIGATION FOR ANY UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME TAX. THE COUNCIL BELIEVES IT HAS APPROPRIATE SUPPORT FOR ANY TAX POSITIONS TAKEN, AND AS SUCH, DOES NOT HAVE ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT ARE MATERIAL TO THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

FINANCIAL AID IS DESIGNED TO ASSIST CURRENTLY REGISTERED GIRL MEMBERS, OR GIRLS SEEKING MEMBERSHIP IN GIRL SCOUTS, BY PROVIDING SUPPLEMENTAL RESOURCES BEYOND A FAMILY'S ABILITY TO PAY. FINANCIAL AID IS PROVIDED BASED ON REQUESTS SUBMITTED VIA AN APPLICATION PROCESS.

GSCCC WILL ACCEPT UNRESTRICTED GIFTS AND GIFTS FOR SPECIFIC PROGRAMS AND PURPOSES, PROVIDED THAT SUCH GIFTS ARE CONSISTENT WITH ITS STATED MISSION, PURPOSES, AND PRIORITIES. GSCCC WILL NOT ACCEPT GIFTS THAT ARE TOO RESTRICTIVE IN PURPOSE. GIFTS THAT ARE TOO RESTRICTIVE ARE THOSE THAT VIOLATE THE TERMS OF THE CORPORATE CHARTER, GIFTS THAT ARE TOO DIFFICULT TO ADMINISTER, OR GIFTS THAT ARE FOR PURPOSES OUTSIDE THE MISSION OF GSCCC. ALL FINAL DECISIONS ON THE RESTRICTIVE NATURE OF A GIFT AND ITS ACCEPTANCE OR REFUSAL SHALL BE MADE BY THE PHILANTHROPY COMMITTEE. THE PHILANTHROPY COMMITTEE IS CHARGED WITH THE RESPONSIBILITY OF REVIEWING ALL GIFTS MADE TO GSCCC, PROPERLY SCREENING AND ACCEPTING THOSE GIFTS, AND MAKING RECOMMENDATIONS TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ON GIFT ACCEPTANCE ISSUES WHEN APPROPRIATE. ALL POTENTIAL OR PROPOSED PLANNED GIFTS OR RESTRICTED GIFTS MAY BE INDIVIDUALLY REVIEWED BY THE CEO, PHILANTHROPY DIRECTOR, AND/OR FINANCE DIRECTOR. PROSPECTIVE DONORS ARE ENCOURAGED TO REQUEST AND MAY EXPECT TO RECEIVE A LETTER REGARDING AGREEMENTS TO RESTRICTIONS PLACED UPON THE PROPOSED GIFT BY THE DONOR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE MEMBERS ELECT DELEGATES WHO IN TURN ELECT MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ARE NOMINATED BY A BOARD DEVELOPMENT COMMITTEE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ARE ELECTED BY DELEGATES FROM THE COUNCIL MEMBERSHIP, 17 WOMEN AND MEN SERVE ON THE GIRL SCOUT COUNCIL OF COLONIAL COAST BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THEY ESTABLISH POLICY, APPROVE BUDGETS, SET DIRECTION FOR THE COUNCIL AND MONITOR PROGRESS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION PROVIDES FORM 990 TO ALL MEMBERS OF THE GOVERNING BODY FOR REVIEW BEFORE FILING THE RETURN.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD IS REQUIRED TO ANNUALLY DISCLOSE ANY CONFLICTS OF INTEREST.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD EVALUATES THE PERFORMANCE AND DETERMINES THE COMPENSATION OF THE CEO. THE BOARD USES COMPARABLE COMPENSATION INFORMATION FROM THE GIRL SCOUTS OF THE USA DURING THE DISCUSSIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND FORM 990 ARE AVAILABLE ON GUIDESTAR, GSCCC'S WEBSITE, AND UPON REQUEST. ALL OTHER DOCUMENTS ARE AVAIABLE UPON REQUEST.

THE ORGANIZATION HAS A COMMITTEE THAT ASSUMES THE RESPONSIBILITY FOR OVERSIGHT OF THE AUDIT AND SELECTION OF AN INDEPENDENT AUDITOR. NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THIS OVERSIGHT OR SELECTION PROCESS IN THE TAX YEAR.
